BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/creative-writing-series-maria-kuznetsova-novelist"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Creative Writing Series: Maria Kuznetsova\, Fiction
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T173000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51534087526177
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the next event in the 2025-2026 Creative Wr
 iting Series: a reading and Q&A featuring novelist Maria Kuznetsova!\n\nTh
 is event is free and open to all\, and will be available in person and liv
 estreamed.\n\n \n\nMaria Kuznetsova was born in Kyiv\, Ukraine\, and moved
  to the United States as a child. She is the author of the novels Oksana\,
  Behave! and Something Unbelievable. An alum of the UC Davis master’s pr
 ogram in creative writing\, she now lives in Auburn\, Alabama\, with her f
 amily\, where she is an associate professor of creative writing at Auburn 
 University. She is also the fiction editor of the Southern Humanities Revi
 ew and her work appears or is forthcoming in dozens of literary journals i
 ncluding One Story\, The Yale Review\, Southern Review\, Threepenny Review
 \, and The Sun.\n\n \n\nThe Creative Writing Series is presented by the UC
  Davis Department of English\, Creative Writing Master of Fine Arts Progra
 m\, and the UC Davis Library.\n\nThe views expressed in this series\, incl
 uding descriptions and biographies\, are those of the speakers and not mea
 nt to represent the views of any other person or institution.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 205
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/creative-writing-series-maria
 -kuznetsova-novelist
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
