X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:From Idea to Impact: Publishing Your Work — Copyright and Other 
 Legal Issues
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T140000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52332281607286
DESCRIPTION:This workshop provides information on owning your work\, from 
 understanding how to retain copyright in your first publications to naviga
 ting the fine print of author agreements. We will explore how to safely in
 corporate third-party copyrighted material into your publication and how t
 o strategically use Creative Commons licenses to dictate how others cite a
 nd share your findings.\n \n\nNo previous experience is required. All disc
 iplines are welcome.\n\n\nPlease register for the Zoom link.\n\nThis six-w
 orkshop series is a collaboration between the library's Scholarly Communic
 ations Program\, the Researcher Services department\, and Blaisdell Medica
 l Library. For any questions\, please contact the Scholarly Communication 
 Officer Michael Ladisch (mladisch@ucdavis.edu). Check our events calendar 
 for more publishing workshops.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copyright-and-other-legal-iss
 ues
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
