BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/ai-literacy-logic-spring-2026"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:AI Literacy & Logic Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T163000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52340792789232
DESCRIPTION:A free 1-day intensive workshop for College of Letters & Scien
 ce majors covering foundational principles and skills for using Artificial
  Intelligence (AI).\n\n \n\nThe landscape of the academic and professional
  world is shifting. Whether you are an aspiring historian\, a budding chem
 ist\, or a future sociologist\, AI is no longer a "tech" skill—it’s a 
 foundational literacy.\n\n \n\nDeveloped through a collaboration between t
 he UC Davis College of Letters & Science and DataLab\, this 1-day intensiv
 e workshop is designed to unveil Artificial Intelligence. We’ve stripped
  away the dense math and complex coding to give you a conceptual\, high-le
 vel understanding of how artificial intelligence systems work\, why they m
 atter\, and how to make them work for you.\n\n \n\nWhy Apply to Attend?\n\
 nIn a single day\, you will move from being a passive AI user to a critica
 l\, strategic collaborator. This training is specifically curated for L&S 
 students to ensure you graduate with the competitive edge needed for the r
 apidly evolving\, AI-driven workplace. According to a LinkedIn survey repo
 rt\, only about a third (38%) of U.S. executives say they're currently hel
 ping their employees become AI-literate. Meanwhile\, findings from a 2025 
 Businesswire study found that 79% of workers feel they must learn new skil
 ls and that AI literacy is the foundation for long-term competitiveness. S
 tudents who attend this all-day workshop and complete required pre- and po
 st-workshop activities will gain foundational and applied skills in AI\, a
 nd receive a certificate of completion.\n\n \n\nNo technical background? N
 o problem. This workshop has no prerequisites. It is designed for thinkers
 \, writers\, and researchers across all liberal arts\, social sciences and
  STEM disciplines.\n\n \n\nThe curriculum is divided into four deep-dive m
 odules:\n\nHow AI Thinks\nUnderstand the "brain" of the machine. We’ll e
 xplore the theories of language and cognition that allow Large Language Mo
 dels (LLMs) to function\, and provide a framework for evaluating their pot
 ential and limits.\n\nHow to Use AI Responsibly\nAI isn't a magic wand—i
 t’s a tool with a history and consequences. We discuss the environmental
  and societal impacts\, how to ensure the veracity of AI results\, and why
  reproducibility is the cornerstone of ethical tech.\n\nHow to Talk with A
 I\nMaster the art and science of prompt engineering. Learn what happens be
 hind the scenes when you send a prompt. Develop sophisticated strategies t
 o get the exact results you need.\n\nHow AI Talks with You\nA look at the 
 future of AI implementation. From simple chatbots to complex autonomous "A
 gents\," learn how AI is being embedded into systems and how to evaluate i
 ts activity.\n\n \n\nBy the end of this one-day workshop\, you will be abl
 e to:\n\nDefine "AI" and distinguish it from traditional statistics and da
 ta science.Identify whether a real-world problem is suitable for an AI sol
 ution.Develop advanced prompting strategies that produce reliable\, useful
  results for your research and career needs.Critically interrogate your ow
 n engagement with AI and its impact on our society and environment.Practic
 e and grow your confidence in using AI in the rapidly evolving\, AI-driven
  workplace. \n\nWho Can Apply?\n\nAll UC Davis undergraduate students with
  majors in the College of Letters & Science are eligible to apply. Registr
 ation priority is given to  Seniors (4th years) and students graduating in
  Spring or Summer 2026.  Other students in the College of Letters & Scienc
 e are encouraged to register and will be admitted as space permits. Accept
 ed learners are expected to attend all modules on their date of instructio
 n.\n\n \n\nApply Now to Participate\n\nThis intensive\, one-day workshop i
 s offered five times during Spring Quarter 2026. Students should apply for
  only one date. Space is limited so don't wait to apply!\n\nRegistering fo
 r a ticket means you are applying to attend. This does not guarantee your 
 participation. Accepted students will receive a confirmation email with th
 e workshop location.Time: 9:00 AM – 4:30 PM with a break for a provided 
 box lunch. Students must plan to attend all modules\, including the networ
 king lunch.Location: In person only. The classroom location will be emaile
 d to accepted students in advance of the workshop.Cost: This workshop is f
 ree for undergraduate students and supported by the UC Davis College of Le
 tters & Science. \n\nQuestions?\n\nReach out to Mark Foncannon at mjfoncan
 non@ucdavis.edu.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/ai-literacy-logic-spring-2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Art in Action": "https://www.meetup.com/art-in-action/events/314058525/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_art_in_action
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Art in Action
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/art-in-action/
UID:event_314058525@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260403T025803Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T150000
SUMMARY:Art in Action: Spectacular Seed Bombs
DESCRIPTION:Pence Family Art Workshops\nLearn about the ancient Japanese p
 ractice of seed bombs! Using air-dry clay and native wildflower seeds\, ma
 ke seed bombs that you can later plant outdoors or in a garden. Decorate y
 our seed bombs with dried petals and stamps\, and design and illustrate a 
 plant care card to help you take care of the wildflowers you plant.\n\nArt
  in Action: Spectacular Seed Bombs\nSaturday\, May 30\, 1-3 PM\n$5 Members
 \, $10 Non-Members (per person\, all materials included)\n\n**How it works
 :**\nArt in Action engages kids in art projects that are fun\, creative\, 
 and collaborative with their family members. This is a drop-in program for
  ages 5-12. No registration in advance is required\, but space and supplie
 s are limited to the first 25 participants and are available on a first co
 me\, first served basis.\n\nWhen you arrive\, pay with cash or card at the
  front desk. A parent or adult caregiver is required to stay\, but only ha
 s to pay for the project for themselves if they are also doing art. Stay a
 s long or as short as you like over the two hour period.\n\nBecome a Membe
 r starting at $70/year and save! If you join the Pence Gallery when you at
 tend this workshop\, you can enjoy Member pricing for Art in Action\, plus
  receive a $5 gift certificate to our gift shop as a thank you. Membership
  supports art for all ages and makes creative moments like this possible
 —jump in and be part of it.\n\nWe have a different Art in Action family 
 workshop every month! Learn more at [https://pencegallery.org/art-in-actio
 n/](https://pencegallery.org/art-in-action/).\n\nThis unique monthly progr
 am is generously sponsored and made possible by Mary Stephens DeWall and L
 es DeWall.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/art-in-action/events/314058525/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260331T190727Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260331T190727Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
